450
00:27:13.852 --> 00:27:17.692
Currently, when to use NAMs is as part of a weight of evidence to better understand

451
00:27:17.712 --> 00:27:21.652
and characterize toxicities when signals were identified and targeted safety

452
00:27:21.812 --> 00:27:24.792
assessment, for example, products in the same class.

453
00:27:25.772 --> 00:27:28.352
And lastly, in parting, we're open to reviewing NAMs.

454
00:27:28.732 --> 00:27:31.752
They may enhance safety assessment while reducing and replacing certain animal

455
00:27:31.812 --> 00:27:34.912
testing. If using NAMs, consult us early.

456
00:27:35.252 --> 00:27:38.592
The timing is important, whether it's for first-in-human,

457
00:27:39.112 --> 00:27:42.552
pre-IND, or later in product development for embryo fetal development studies.

458
00:27:43.001 --> 00:27:46.852
And generally, there's more flexibility when included

